# Rust
/target
**/*.rs.bk

# Toolchain + cargo home relocated into the project dir (off the nearly-full C:).
# These are large, machine-local, and must never be committed.
/.cargo/
/.rustup/

# Secrets — local publishing tokens (crates.io / npm / winget PAT). NEVER commit.
# A committed `.env.example` (no secrets) would still be allowed by these rules.
.env
.env.local
.env.*.local

# insta pending snapshots (accepted snapshots ARE committed)
*.pending-snap

# Generated flamegraph SVGs (`skiagram flame --out ...`) — output artifacts, not committed.
/skiagram-flame.svg
/spend.svg

# Internal-only working docs — kept locally for project context, never published.
/CLAUDE.md
/PUBLISHING.md
/STATUS.md

# OS noise
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
